  <thing id="fS2DistMvt" name="Disturbing Movements" description="The disjointed, uneven, jerky way you move strains the mind of those who see you.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} 2 HD, undead type, Cha 13.\n\n{b}Benefit:{/b} The obviously unnatural style of your movements is unsettling if seen clearly. Whenever you take a full attack action or a full move action, all non-undead within 30 feet who are able to see you must make Will saves (DC 10 + 1/2 your HD + your Cha modifier) or be shaken for 2d4 rounds. This ability does not stack with other fear effects (it never creates conditions worse than shaken), and a creature can only fail its saving throw against this ability once per day. This is a mind-affecting fear effect." compset="Feat" summary="The disjointed, uneven, jerky way you move strains the mind of those who see you." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>From SGG - 7 Feats for the Undead</comment>
    <usesource source="srcAoW"/>
